{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: ...until he dropped his winnings back and gave up a million of his own cash.
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ICHIKAWA, hours later, his chips depleted.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ACE and SHERBERT still watch from behind the barrier as millions in chips are back in the dealer's racks.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: In the casino, the cardinal rule is to keep them playing...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Move in on ACE as he smokes a cigarette.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: ...and keep them coming back.
{DIALOGUE}: The longer they play, the more they lose.
{DIALOGUE}: In the end, we get it all.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. TANGIERS CASINO - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ACE, with pit bosses next to him, looks out over the huge casino where hundreds of thousands of dollars are being poured into machines.
