{META_DATA}: (To MIKE)
{DIALOGUE}: Don't make us come lookin' for you.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MIKE
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, you won't have to look for me.
{DIALOGUE}: I appreciate it.
{DIALOGUE}: Thanks, Nicky.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NICKY
{DIALOGUE}: All right, Mike.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MIKE gets up from the table.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NICKY (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: They were degenerate gamblers, coke freaks.
{DIALOGUE}: In no time, I had half the dealers in the Tangiers in my pocket.
{DIALOGUE}: Then...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. TANGIERS POKER TABLE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: NICKY is at a table with his gang of card sharks: SLIM, ROCKY, MOOSH and COWBOY, all secretly signaling each other, sandbagging a mark.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MIKE, the crooked dealer from the previous scene, deals NICKY a winning hand.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NICKY (V.O.)
