{DIALOGUE}: Charlie M!
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. TANGIERS CASINO - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Extreme close-up of a slot-machine.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Four reels with sevens across.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Suddenly, the power goes out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lights die down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Machine 'waaaooows' down to a dead stop.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Security guards, on their hands and knees, are pulling the plugs on the three giant $15,000 progressive machines, as ACE talks to DON WARD.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: Four reels, sevens across, three fifteen-thousand-dollar jackpots?
{DIALOGUE}: Do you have any idea what the odds are?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WARD
{DIALOGUE}: Shoot, it's gotta be in the millions, maybe more.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: Three fuckin' jackpots in twenty minutes?
{DIALOGUE}: Why didn't you pull the machines?
{DIALOGUE}: Why didn't you call me?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WARD
{DIALOGUE}: Well, it happened so quick.
{DIALOGUE}: Three guys won.
{DIALOGUE}: I didn't have a chance to call you.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: You didn't see the scam?
{DIALOGUE}: You didn't see what was goin' on?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WARD
{DIALOGUE}: Well, there's no way to determine that, Sam.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, there is.
{DIALOGUE}: An infallible way!
{DIALOGUE}: They won!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WARD
{DIALOGUE}: Well, it's a casino.
{DIALOGUE}: People gotta win sometimes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: Hey... Ward, you're pissin' me off.
{DIALOGUE}: Now, you're insulting my intelligence.
{DIALOGUE}: What do you think, I'm a fuckin' idiot?
{DIALOGUE}: You know goddamn well somebody had to get into those machines and set those fuckin' reels.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SHERBERT enters, stands next to ACE.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: The probability on one-four-reel machine is a million and a half to one.
{DIALOGUE}: On three machines in a row, it's in the billions.
{DIALOGUE}: It cannot happen... would not happen, you fuckin' momo!
{DIALOGUE}: What's the matter with you!
{DIALOGUE}: Didn't you see you were bein' set up on the second win?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WARD
{DIALOGUE}: I really think you're -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{META_DATA}: (Interrupts)
{DIALOGUE}: You - Wait!
{DIALOGUE}: You didn't see that you were being set up on the second win?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WARD
{DIALOGUE}: I really think you're overreacting in this whole -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{META_DATA}: (Interrupts)
{DIALOGUE}: Listen, you fuckin' yokel, I've had it with you.
{DIALOGUE}: I've been carryin' your ass in this place ever since I got here.
{DIALOGUE}: Get your ass and get your things and get out of here.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WARD
{DIALOGUE}: You're firin' me?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: I'm firin' you?
{DIALOGUE}: No, I'm not firin'
{META_DATA}: (mocking WARD)
{DIALOGUE}: I'm firin' you, you -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gives SHERBERT a look.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WARD
{DIALOGUE}: You might regret this, Mr Rothstein.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: I'll regret it even more if I keep you on.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WARD
{DIALOGUE}: This is not the way to treat people.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: Listen, if you didn't know you're bein' scammed, you're too fuckin' dumb to keep this job.
{DIALOGUE}: If you did know, you were in on it.
{DIALOGUE}: Either way, you're out!
{DIALOGUE}: Get out!
{DIALOGUE}: Go on.
{META_DATA}: (To SHERBERT.)
{DIALOGUE}: Let's go.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ACE and SHERBERT walk off, WARD turns to leave.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. TANGIERS CASINO, AKU-AKU LOUNGE - DAY, AN HOUR LATER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ACE and GREEN are seated having coffee and muffins in the Hawaiian lounge by the casino floor.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: I mean, the guy is history as far as I'm concerned.
{DIALOGUE}: History.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GREEN
{DIALOGUE}: But you can't just fire him.
{DIALOGUE}: Webb's his brother-in-law.
{DIALOGUE}: He's County Commissioner.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: So what?
{DIALOGUE}: Everybody out here with cowboy boots is a fuckin' county commissioner or related to a county commissioner.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm fuckin' sick of it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GREEN
{DIALOGUE}: This is his state.
{DIALOGUE}: His uncle's Chief Judge.
{DIALOGUE}: His brother-in-law runs the County Commission.
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know how many other relatives he's got in town.
{DIALOGUE}: There's gotta be a way to work him back in.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: Phil, I can understand.
{DIALOGUE}: You're in the finances, you're upstairs, but you are not on the floor.
{DIALOGUE}: I got thousands of players.
{DIALOGUE}: I got five hundred dealers.
{DIALOGUE}: They're all lookin' to rob me blind, twenty-four hours a day.
{DIALOGUE}: I have to let them know I'm watching all the details, all the time; that there is not one single thing I will not catch as I am over here.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Breaks open his blueberry muffin, puts it down and points to Green's.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: Look at yours.
