{DIALOGUE}: He's got lots of friends here.
{DIALOGUE}: Now, his family and their money go back many, many years.
{DIALOGUE}: Now, friends vote... family and money votes.
{DIALOGUE}: That's important to me... and you.
{DIALOGUE}: And if you'll think about our little problem along them lines... and you forgive me for sayin' it, maybe he did not deserve to be fired.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: I'm sorry, but he knew about our gettin' hit on three big machines in a row and he did nothing about it.
{DIALOGUE}: That means either he was in on it or, forgive me for saying this, he was too dumb to see what was going on.
{DIALOGUE}: Either way, I cannot have a man like that workin' here.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WEBB
{DIALOGUE}: Before we point the dirty end of the stick at 'ol Don, uh, we better be sure we can prove them charges.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: Believe me, if I could prove it, he would be under arrest.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WEBB
{DIALOGUE}: Are, uh -
{META_DATA}: (Clears throat.)
{DIALOGUE}: - are we certain that you want the Gamin' Control Board eyeballin' your record and your gangster pals like Nicky Santoro?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: I think you're way out of line talkin' to me like that.
{DIALOGUE}: What you're sayin' is libelous, and you're in no position to challenge my expertise.
{DIALOGUE}: I went way out of my way to be very helpful and courteous to that kid.
{DIALOGUE}: He's weak, he's incompetent.
{DIALOGUE}: He jeopardizes the whole place.
{DIALOGUE}: There's not much more I can do for him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WEBB
{META_DATA}: (Chuckling)
{DIALOGUE}: You have got me there.
{DIALOGUE}: Old Don is as useless as tits on a boar.
{META_DATA}: (Chuckles.)
{DIALOGUE}: But, he is my brother-in-law, and I would look on it as a personal favor if you'd think some more on hirin' him back.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: I can't do that.
{DIALOGUE}: And I appreciate the fact that he's your brother-in- law, and I do want to help you and I like to do favors, and I know who you are, but I cannot do that.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WEBB
{DIALOGUE}: Well, could there be any position... further down the trough?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{META_DATA}: (Pause)
{DIALOGUE}: I'm sorry, I can't do anything.
{DIALOGUE}: He's too incompetent.
{DIALOGUE}: And the bottom line is, he cannot be trusted.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The telephone rings.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ACE picks it up.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{META_DATA}: (Into telephone)
{DIALOGUE}: Okay, thanks.
{META_DATA}: (To WEBB.)
{DIALOGUE}: Um... you know, that's it.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm sorry.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WEBB
{DIALOGUE}: Mr Rothstein.
{DIALOGUE}: Your people never will understand the way it works out here.
{DIALOGUE}: You're all just our guests.
{DIALOGUE}: But you act like you're at home.
{DIALOGUE}: Let me tell you somethin', partner... you ain't home.
{DIALOGUE}: But that's where we're gonna send you if it harelips the Governor.
{META_DATA}: (Pause.)
{DIALOGUE}: Thank you for your time.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: No problem.
{META_DATA}: (Getting up and shaking hands.)
{DIALOGUE}: Sorry.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WEBB
{META_DATA}: (Smiles slightly)
{DIALOGUE}: You bet.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ACE'S HOUSE, BATHROOM/BEDROOM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ACE, in pain from his ulcer, opens a bottle of pills in his bathroom and sees that it is almost empty.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: What happened to my pills?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He leaves the bathroom and walks into the bedroom where GINGER is stretched out on their imperial bed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GINGER
{DIALOGUE}: Huh?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{META_DATA}: (Waving the pill bottle)
{DIALOGUE}: Isn't it bad enough you're drinkin' too much, you're takin' all my pills too?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GINGER
{DIALOGUE}: I didn't take your pills.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: Look - for my ulcer, I take a half a one of these, a half a one of these.
{DIALOGUE}: And that's when I have extreme pain.
{DIALOGUE}: I had a three-month supply.
{DIALOGUE}: What'd you do with 'em?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GINGER
