{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CONTROL BOARD LOBBY - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Putting on his sunglasses, ACE emerges from the courtroom with SHERBERT, GINGER, OSCAR and several reporters.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is surrounded by the press.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FEMALE NEWSCASTER (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: ...stunned commissioners into the hallway, where he continued his harangue until his own lawyers and friends urged him to leave.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: (To COMMISSIONERS standing in the hallway, speaking into a TV news microphone) We all have a past.
{DIALOGUE}: You have a past, I have a past.
{DIALOGUE}: And my past is no worse than yours.
{DIALOGUE}: But you guys think you have the right to pass judgement on me.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FEMALE NEWSCASTER (V.O.)
{META_DATA}: (Overlapping)
{DIALOGUE}: Long suspected of running the Tangiers without...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{META_DATA}: (Overlapping)
{DIALOGUE}: ...twenty years in order to find nothin' on me -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OSCAR pulls him away, ACE looks back at the COMMISSIONERS.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: - unsubstantiated truths on me.
{DIALOGUE}: And if you look at your own lives you'd all be in jail.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OSCAR ushers ACE out, past WEBB and Gaming Investigator AUSTIN.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FEMALE NEWSCASTER (V.O.)
{META_DATA}: (Overlapping)
{DIALOGUE}: ...a gaming license, yesterday's hearing was to determine whether someone with Rothstein's checkered personal history was qualified to officially hold the top gaming post.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT./EXT. GAGGI'S CAR, BACK HOME ALLEY - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: GAGGI hands STONE an issue of the Las Vegas Sun showing a photograph of ACE at the licensing hearing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Headline reads: 'Rothstein out of gaming: Control Board Rules against Rothstein License Application'.
