{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He drives off.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. DESERT SCENE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A solitary ACE waiting in the vast desert, looking around.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ACE looks at a sage brush and sand and a few rocks on the desert floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This could be a hole meant for him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He steps away from it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Meeting in the middle of the desert always made me nervous.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's a scary place.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: I knew about the holes in the desert, of course, and everywhere I looked, there could have been a hole.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. DESERT ROAD - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Aerial shot of NICKY driving.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Normally, my prospects of comin' back alive from a meeting with Nicky were ninety-nine out of a hundred.
{DIALOGUE}: But this time, when I heard him say, 'A couple a hundred yards down the road', I gave myself fifty-fifty.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. DESERT - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ACE still standing in the desert.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: NICKY's car suddenly appears as a reflection in ACE's sunglasses, shaking ACE out of his desert-induced reverie.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: NICKY's car pulls up by ACE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He gets out and storms up to him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NICKY
{DIALOGUE}: Where the fuck you get off talkin' to people about me behind my back?
{DIALOGUE}: Goin' over my head?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: What people?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NICKY
{DIALOGUE}: What people!
{DIALOGUE}: What'd you think, I wasn't gonna find out?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: I don't even know what you're talkin' about, Nick.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NICKY
{DIALOGUE}: No?
{DIALOGUE}: You said I'm bringin' heat on you?!
{DIALOGUE}: I gotta listen to people because of your fuckin' shit?!
{DIALOGUE}: You're ordering me out?!
{DIALOGUE}: You better get your own fuckin' army, pal!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: I didn't do anything.
{DIALOGUE}: I mean, I didn't order you or anybody... I only told Andy Stone that you had a lot of heat on you, and that was a problem.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NICKY
{DIALOGUE}: You want me to get out of my own fuckin' town?!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, I said I - let the bullshit blow over for a while so I can run the casino.
{DIALOGUE}: Anything goes wrong with the casino, it's my ass.
{DIALOGUE}: It's not yours, it's my ass.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NICKY
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, I don't know whether you know this or not, but you only have your fuckin' casino because I made that possible!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: I -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NICKY
{META_DATA}: (Interrupting)
{DIALOGUE}: I'm what counts out here!
{DIALOGUE}: Not your fuckin' country clubs or your fuckin' TV shows!
{DIALOGUE}: And what the fuck are you doin' on TV anyhow?!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: What are you -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NICKY
{META_DATA}: (Interrupting)
{DIALOGUE}: You know I get calls from back home every fuckin' day?!
{DIALOGUE}: They think you went batshit!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: I'm only on TV because I gotta be able to hang around the casino.
{DIALOGUE}: You understand that.
{DIALOGUE}: You know that.
{DIALOGUE}: Come on.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NICKY
{DIALOGUE}: Your fuckin' ass!
{DIALOGUE}: You could have had the food and beverage job without goin' on television!
{DIALOGUE}: You wanted to go on TV.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, I did want to go on TV.
{DIALOGUE}: That way I have a forum.
{DIALOGUE}: I can fight back.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm known.
{DIALOGUE}: People see me.
{DIALOGUE}: They know they can't fuck around with me like they could if I was an unknown.
{DIALOGUE}: That's right.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NICKY
{DIALOGUE}: You're makin' a big fuckin' spectacle of yourself.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: Me?!
{DIALOGUE}: I wouldn't even be in this situation if it wasn't for you.
{DIALOGUE}: You brought down so much fuckin' heat on me.
{DIALOGUE}: I mean, every time I meet somebody here, the big question is do I know you.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NICKY
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, sure.
{DIALOGUE}: Now you want to blame your fuckin' license on me, is that it?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: No, it - it - Nicky, when you asked me if you could come out here, what did I tell you?
{DIALOGUE}: I mean, you asked me, and I knew you were going to come out no matter what I said, but what did I tell you?
{DIALOGUE}: Do you remember what I told...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NICKY
{META_DATA}: (Interrupting)
{DIALOGUE}: Back -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{DIALOGUE}: ...you?
{DIALOGUE}: Do you remember what I told you?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NICKY
{DIALOGUE}: Back - Back up, back up a fuckin' minute here.
{DIALOGUE}: One minute.
{DIALOGUE}: I asked you?!
{DIALOGUE}: When the fuck did I ever ask you if I could come out here?!
{DIALOGUE}: Get this through your head, you -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACE
{META_DATA}: (Interrupting)
{DIALOGUE}: You never - ?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NICKY
{DIALOGUE}: Get this through your head, you Jew motherfucker, you.
{DIALOGUE}: You only exist out here because of me!
{DIALOGUE}: That's the only reason!
{DIALOGUE}: Without me, you, personally, every fuckin' wiseguy skell [Skell: the lowest form of wiseguy - a drunken bum] around'll take a piece of your fuckin' Jew ass!
{DIALOGUE}: Then where you gonna go?!
{DIALOGUE}: You're fuckin' warned!
{DIALOGUE}: Don't ever go over my fuckin' head again!
{DIALOGUE}: You motherfucker, you!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: NICKY drives off, leaving an angry and frustrated ACE to ponder the desert and the holes.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. JUBILATION NIGHTCLUB - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Overhead of ACE, OSCAR, SHERBERT, TRUDY and showgirls walking down the zebra pattern carpet of the nightclub.
